commit.message:
tests: normalize test output on python3.11

instead of

    test1 (tests.MyTest) ... ok
    test2 (tests.MyTest) ... ok
    test3 (tests.MyTest) ... FAIL

on python3.11 this is displayed as:

    test1 (tests.MyTest.test1) ... ok
    test2 (tests.MyTest.test2) ... ok
    test3 (tests.MyTest.test3) ... FAIL
update pyinstaller to 6.1.0 for python >= 3.11 support

commit.message: fix a bunch of release mechanism bugs

replace non-working coverage badge

This uses a (monkey-patched) badge generator to create the coverage
badge instead of a service that is no longer updating the coverage
badge.

remove Travis CI

Since GitHub has CI facilities now, we'll use those instead.

re-add Python version specifiers

I decided it is probably helpful for people to see the versions of
Python the project supports.
rework project to match my more recent preferences
